p: A total of 27 compounds were characterized in DCEO, representing 82.2% of the total essential oil ( Figure S1). According to the results obtained from GC–MS analysis ( Table S1), the main constituents in DCEO were benzaldehyde (4.37%), cycloundecene (E) (2.36%), α-terpineol (2.96%), β-bisabolene (4.71%), dehydro-β-ionone (28.43%), n-hexadecanoic acid (9.21%), and oleic acid (6.20%).
